10/01/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Top EU officials are expected to arrive in Sarajevo next week for Wednesday's (15 January) official ceremony marking the beginning of the EU Police Mission's (EUPM) work in BiH. 
EU security chief Javier Solana and Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou, whose country now presides over the Union, are expected to attend, as is High Representative Paddy Ashdown. 
The EUPM assumed the task of police monitoring and restructuring from the UN on 1 January. 
On Thursday, Bulgaria signed an agreement to participate in the mission. 
(OHR Sources - 10/01/03; NTV Hayat, BTA - 09/01/03)
